<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATIONAL VIDEO RENTALS ; 'FUGITIVE' JUST KEEPS ON RUNNING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One of these weeks, "The Fugitive" will finally run out of gas. But its 
top-of-the-chart status continues, even though some retailers are reporting 
rentals are down somewhat from the huge early numbers."Cool Runnings," No. 5 
after two weeks, seems to have cornered the comedy market. Featuring the late 
John Candy, the Disneyesque spin on the story of Jamaica's Olympic bobsled team 
is one of only two comedies in the Top 15. The other, "The Beverly 
Hillbillies," isn't tickling that many funny bones. It hasn't made much 
progress in three weeks, holding at No. 13. Debuts: "Another Stakeout," with 
Richard Dreyfuss, at No. 17, and "Mr. Jones," starring Richard Gere, No. 20.  
</P>
<P>
 * Don't let the low (No. 38) rental-chart debut fool you. "Mrs. Doubtfire" 
really is a big video hit. One reason for the low opening is that it's also on 
the sales market, discounted to $14-$15 in many outlets. So the hard-core fans 
are buying it rather than renting. It should move into the Top 5 next week. 
