<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; SEA KINGS EARN SHARE OF THE TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Corona del Mar upset eighth-ranked Newport Harbor in five games Thursday, 
helping the Sea Kings earn a share of the Sea View League boys' volleyball 
title. 
</P>
<P>
 Brooks Hoppe had 26 kills and Brad Callahan added 12 to lead the Sea Kings to 
a 3-15, 15-4, 15-8, 11-15, 15-6 victory at Newport Harbor High. 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar (14-2, 12-2 in league) lost to Newport Harbor in four games 
during their first match, so Newport Harbor will be the league's top-seeded 
team for the Southern Section playoffs, which begin May 13. 
</P>
<P>
 Although Mitch McCoy had a match-high 28 kills for Newport Harbor (13-4, 
12-2), the Sailors were sluggish after an easy 15-3 victory in Game 1. 
</P>
<P>
 In Game 2, Hoppe and Brian Coleman had three kills each to help Corona del Mar 
take an 11-1 lead. In Game 3, Hoppe and McCoy had eight kills each, but the Sea 
Kings won eight of the last 10 points to take a two-games-to-one lead. 
</P>
<P>
 McCoy's jump serve helped the Sailors win five consecutive points to take an 
11-8 lead in Game 4. Newport Harbor won to force a fifth game. 
</P>
<P>
 But the Sea Kings took a 10-3 lead in Game 5 and closed out the match with 
three points on three consecutive Newport Harbor errors. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
