<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA CHRISTIAN MUST FORFEIT EIGHT VICTORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southern California Christian's baseball team will forfeit eight victories 
because high school officials discovered it had been using an ineligible 
player, Coach Bert Esposito said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Flames, the third-ranked team in Division VI, had their record changed to 
5-12-1 from 13-4-1.They beat La Verne Lutheran, 2-1, Thursday to improve to 
6-12-1, 2-5 in the Arrowhead League. 
</P>
<P>
 "We hope the section will allow us to compete in the playoffs as a wild-card 
team now," Esposito said. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 After three seasons, Tony McCabe has resigned as Fullerton boys' basketball 
coach, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Indians were 30-22 under McCabe, who plans to return to Cal State 
Fullerton to complete his master's degree in physical education. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm taking a year off, just to step back," said McCabe, who also coached 
cross-country last season. "I've been coaching for 14 years, maybe I was a 
little burned out." MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
