<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Stanford volleyball player Matt Fuerbringer, a former standout at Estancia, 
was named to the American Volleyball Coaches Assn. All-American team. 
Fuerbringer is a freshman outside hitter for the Cardinal. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Ralph, an All-South Coast League outfielder from Dana Hills, has 
committed to play for Harvard, his father, Ed, said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ralph had scholarship offers from Notre Dame and Santa Clara. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Bryan Dunagan, a sophomore pitcher from Fullerton College, signed a letter of 
intent to play at Pacific, Hornet Coach Nick Fuscardo said. 
</P>
<P>
 A right-hander, Dunagan is 2-4 with a 4.47 earned-run average in 46 1/3 
innings. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Two local swimmers, Monica Huszcz of Irvine High and Ian Pyka of El Toro, will 
attend Cal Poly San Luis Obispo, Irvine Novaquatics Coach David Salo announced. 
</P>
<P>
 Huszcz swims the 500 and 200 freestyle events. Pyka swims the breaststroke and 
individual medley. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College announced the signing of Mike Guevara, a former 
Santa Margarita basketball standout who played the last two seasons at Cardinal 
Stritch, an NAIA school in Milwaukee. 
</P>
<P>
 Guevara, a 6-foot point guard, was third in the county in assists in 1991, his 
senior year at Santa Margarita. Last year at Cardinal Stritch, he averaged 14 
points and six assists. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon's Lance Eddy and Woodbridge's Alan Dugard have been named coaches for 
the third North-South All-Star Softball game June 8 at Brea-Olinda High. 
</P>
<P>
 Eddy will direct the North and Dugard the South in the game, which will 
feature the county's best seniors. 
</P>
