NATION IN BRIEF; NEW YORK; U.S. LINKS BLAST, KAHANE MURDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Federal prosecutors revealed details for the first time of an alleged 
international conspiracy that links three of the men convicted in the World 
Trade Center blast to the murder of radical Rabbi Meir Kahane.The government 
released previously confidential information in a 100-page document ahead of 
the trial in New York of radical Islamic Sheik Omar Abdul Rahman and a group of 
others charged with conspiring to wage a war of urban terrorism against the 
United States through bombings and assassinations. The papers, which provide a 
preview of the government's case, include excerpts from tapes in which Abdul 
Rahman was told of and advocated Islamic paramilitary camps in the United 
States. The trial is scheduled for September. 
