<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; 2ND MAN CHARGED IN '92 RAPE-SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A second man has been charged in connection with a 2-year-old Oxnard murder in 
which the first defendant has been sentenced to die in the gas chamber, 
prosecutors announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Frederick Lee Jackson, 26, faces charges of murder, rape and kidnaping in the 
Jan. 26, 1992, slaying of 30-year-old Genoveva Gonzales, a mother of four. 
</P>
<P>
 The murder charge against Jackson includes a special allegation that Gonzales 
was shot while being kidnaped and raped. If convicted of the special 
allegation, Jackson could be sent to the gas chamber. 
</P>
<P>
 Christopher James Sattiewhite, 24, was sentenced April 25 to die in the gas 
chamber for his role in Gonzales' death. A jury convicted him of the same 
charges that Jackson faces. 
</P>
<P>
 However, prosecutors acknowledge that their case against Sattiewhite was 
stronger than the case against Jackson. Sattiewhite admitted to being the 
triggerman. 
</P>
<P>
 Other than that fact, "95% of the evidence is the same," Deputy Dist. Atty. 
Donald C. Glynn said. 
</P>
<P>
 Glynn said a decision on whether to seek the death penalty against Jackson 
will not be made for at least a month. Jackson is serving a 28-year sentence in 
an unrelated rape case. DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
