<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; POLICE BLOCK PARTY TO FEATURE 180 BOOTHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura Police Department will hold its annual block party Saturday, 
hoping to teach residents about public safety issues and give demonstrations on 
everything from pepper spray to fingerprinting. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's kind of like a mini street fair, but it's all geared toward public 
safety," Ventura Police Lt. Steve Bowman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The third annual block party will feature about 180 booths and exhibits on 
crime prevention, personal safety and other public safety issues. The event is 
free and will be held at police and fire headquarters at 1425 Dowell Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is intended to foster community support for the Police Department 
and encourage residents to talk to officers, Bowman said.  
</P>
<P>
 Festivities will begin at 8 a.m. with a pancake breakfast sponsored by the 
Ventura Suburban Kiwanis Club and opening ceremonies start at 8:30 a.m. The 
event is scheduled to last until 5 p.m. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
