<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: MUSICIANS TO BE ALLOWED TO UNIONIZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After three months of negotiations and the threat of a possible strike, the 
board of the Ventura County Symphony signed an agreement Thursday allowing its 
musicians to unionize. 
</P>
<P>
 "We will begin negotiations to achieve a collective bargaining agreement that 
will be recognized by the American Federation of Musicians," said Steve 
Thiroux, spokesman for the Ventura County Symphony Musicians. 
</P>
<P>
 The musicians had threatened to strike this weekend, when the symphony is 
scheduled to perform its final season concert at Oxnard Civic Auditorium, 
unless management allowed them representation by Musicians Union Local 581. 
</P>
<P>
 About 1,300 people are expected to attend the concert Saturday, said Karine 
Beesley, the symphony's executive director. 
</P>
<P>
 Beesley said the symphony's board of directors had not agreed to allow the 
musicians to unionize prior to Thursday because the board needed to clarify 
some portions of the agreement. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
