<P>
 In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos 2, El Dorado 0 -- Two infield singles and Michelle Schneider's 
two-run triple provided the offense for second-ranked Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
 Schneider, batting .411, had two hits as the Griffins (19-4, 8-0) beat El 
Dorado pitcher Heather Hamer (9-4) for the third time. 
</P>
<P>
 Debbie Wilson (13-1) matched Hamer with a six-hitter and was tough with 
runners on base; the visiting Golden Hawks (17-7, 6-2) had a runner in scoring 
position four times and had a runner at third in the last three innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos clinched a share of the league title with two games to play. 
Second-place El Dorado played its third game in three days, including a 2-0 
victory over fifth-ranked Cypress on Wednesday. MARTIN HENDERSON 
