<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CYPRESS CLINCHES TIE FOR CONFERENCE BASEBALL TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cypress clinched at least a tie for the Orange Empire Conference baseball 
championship with a 17-4 victory over Golden West Thursday in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory keeps Cypress (33-10, 18-5 in conference) one game ahead of 
Riverside with one left.But because Cypress holds a 3-1 advantage over 
Riverside in head-to-head meetings, the Chargers are assured of being seeded 
first in the playoffs. Riverside beat Rancho Santiago, 16-4, Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is a tough (conference) to win," Cypress Coach Scott Pickler said. "I 
was telling (assistant coach) Bill (Pinkham) I thought we would battle for 
third place." 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress led, 5-0, going into the eighth but the Chargers added 12 runs, nine 
coming after two were out. Andy Gonzales capped the inning with a three-run 
home run. Jason Hodges had an RBI double and a two-run single also in the 
eighth for Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress got a solid pitching performance from starter Aaron France, a 
sophomore right-hander who has signed to attend Miami next fall. France (10-3) 
gave up four hits and struck out five in seven innings. France walked three but 
none after the third inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress plays host to Saddleback and Rancho Santiago is at Riverside at noon 
Saturday in conference-ending games. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
