<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: CSUN'S HEITMANN NAMED VOLLEYBALL ALL-AMERICAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The American Volleyball Coaches Assn. named Cal State Northridge middle 
blocker Oliver Heitmann an NCAA Division I second-team All-American on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Heitmann is a 6-foot-7 junior from Hamburg, Germany.Forty players were 
nominated for the All-American teams. UCLA and Stanford each had three players 
on the first or second team. 
</P>
<P>
 The team was selected by a panel of AVCA coaches. Baseball  
</P>
<P>
 P.C. Shaw, an assistant baseball coach at Cal State Northridge, will serve as 
an assistant this summer with the Wausau Woodchucks of the Northwoods League. 
</P>
<P>
 Northwoods is a collegiate summer league that uses wood bats. Northridge 
catcher-outfielder Josh Smaler is expected to play for the team, which is 
coached by San Jose State assistant Scott Hertler. Volleyball  
</P>
<P>
 Westlake High's Stephanie Salm has committed to play for Harvard. Salm, a 
5-foot-9 senior setter, also considered Yale and Northwestern. Track & Field  
</P>
<P>
 The Northridge Open, scheduled to take place Saturday at Cal State Northridge, 
has been canceled because preliminary work on a new track at Northridge is 
scheduled to begin this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge Coach Don Strametz said that athletes who already have registered 
for the meet are eligible to compete in the Cal Poly Pomona Invitational on 
Saturday. Miscellany  
</P>
<P>
 The City of Moorpark Department of Community Services will begin registration 
Monday for summer sports leagues, including men's, women's and co-ed softball, 
co-ed volleyball and men's basketball. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (805) 529-6864, ext. 231. 
</P>
