<P>
WORKERS UNEARTH BODY IN SAN MARINO YARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Workers digging a hole Thursday for a back yard pool in San Marino unearthed 
the skeletal remains of a person whose body had been dismembered and buried in 
three plastic bags, a Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The remains were uncovered behind the Lorain Road home about 1 p.m., said 
Sheriff's Deputy Rich Erickson.  
</P>
<P>
 Detectives could not immediately determine the age or sex of the body. They 
said they would return to the home today to look for clues.  
</P>
<P>
 The nine-year resident of the home was not considered a suspect in the case. 
</P>
