<TEXT>
<P>
 Jay Leno on why the woman who says she will sue President Clinton for sex 
harassment while he was governor in 1991 didn't come forward sooner: 
</P>
<P>
 The woman said: "Well, the line was so long." 
</P>
<P>
 Leno on the announcement that the Rolling Stones are going back on tour: 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't know if they are getting old, but . . . their opening act is Victor 
Borge." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 After Burt Reynolds collapsed on the set of "Evening Shade," tests showed 
nothing conclusive. The Gags Gang at Funny Stuff newsletter reports that 
doctors did find that his blood count and net worth were both dangerously low. 
Loni Anderson rushed to the hospital to comfort Burt . . . and to make sure 
that his wallet was on life-support systems. 
</P>
