<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CYPRESS; SUSPECT HELD IN RAPE ATTEMPT ON GIRL, 7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRIAN RAY BALLOU 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man was arrested after he allegedly tried to lure a 7-year-old girl from her 
front yard and attempted to rape her, authorities said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl, who was unharmed in the Tuesday night attack, told police she 
managed to free herself from Emilio Solares Paz, 22, shortly after he pulled 
her behind some bushes next to her house near the intersection of Myra Avenue 
and Rodeo Court. 
</P>
<P>
 She said Paz, who was riding a bicycle, stopped in front of her house about 9 
p.m. and tried to talk her into going behind the bushes. When she refused, Paz 
grabbed her, dragged her behind the bushes, and tried to pull her clothes off, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl said that when Paz attempted to pull her clothes off, she escaped and 
ran home to tell her parents, who then notified police. 
</P>
<P>
 "After a short search, we found him about a quarter-mile from the incident 
hiding behind a trailer," Police Lt. Jim Weuve said. Weuve said the girl, who 
had been playing in her front yard before the incident, identified Paz as her 
attacker. 
</P>
<P>
 Paz was arrested on suspicion of kidnaping, child molestation and attempted 
rape, police said. He was being held at Orange County Jail on $50,000 bail. 
BRIAN RAY BALLOU 
</P>
</TEXT>
