<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE NEXT 'GERALDO': SUSPECTS CAUGHT WHEN APPEARING ON TV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A panelist at a taping of the "Geraldo" television show was arrested Thursday 
after a Westminster police department employee at the taping recognized him as 
a suspect in a pizza parlor robbery. 
</P>
<P>
 The police employee, who was on his day off, remembered 23-year-old Glen Allen 
Bouscher from a photo lineup of robbery suspects he had put together just 
Wednesday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The employee called Westminster detectives investigating the robbery and said, 
"Your suspect is on 'Geraldo,' " according to Westminster Police Lt. Bill 
Lewis. "That's the guy I put in the line-up."  
</P>
<P>
 The detectives contacted Los Angeles police in the Wilshire Division who 
arrived at the Los Angeles studio before the show was over. They arrested 
Bouscher of El Centro after the taping. No one was injured in the February 
robbery. 
</P>
<P>
 Bouscher is in the Orange County Jail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
