<HEADLINE>
<P>
8 ARE INJURED IN HIT-AND-RUN CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A hit-and-run driver crashed into a car, injuring its eight occupants, police 
said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the second car, Eloy Mendoza, 19, of Panorama City, was treated 
for cuts to his forehead and legs at Valley Presbyterian Hospital in Van Nuys 
and released. 
</P>
<P>
 Seven others, including a 4-year-old girl, who suffered bruises and complained 
of pain, were treated at local hospitals and released Wednesday, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 9:15 p.m. Wednesday when the driver of a four-door 
gold Chevrolet Caprice traveling north on Woodley Avenue near Vanowen Steet in 
Van Nuys rear-ended the car carrying the eight occupants and sped away. 
</P>
<P>
 The car with eight occupants crashed into the car in front of it. That car 
also left the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 Police had no suspects late Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
