<P>
 The junior left fielder and second baseman has multiple hits in six games and 
leads the team with a .415 batting average and .566 slugging percentage. He 
leads Bell-Jeff with 22 hits in 53 at-bats. 
</P>
<P>
 "That's incredible for a leadoff guy," coach Craig Sherwood said. "He's the 
reason we're doing so well lately. He has speed, power and consistency." Around 
the Leagues. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 * Antelope Valley freshman Kevin Barlow, the team's starting third baseman, 
had seven hits in eight at-bats last week. 
</P>
