stretch. The team went 2-2. 
</P>
<P>
 * Chatsworth shortstop Bryan LaCour went six for eight last week to hike his 
average to .500. The Chancellors have won 13 consecutive games. 
</P>
<P>
 * In 97 plate appearances, Harvard-Westlake's Jon Schaeffer has been hit by a 
pitch or drawn a walk 32 times. The Stanford-bound senior catcher is hitting 
.492, which gives him an on-base percentage of .690. 
</P>
<P>
 * Chaminade may have one of the Mission League's best pitchers -- sophomore 
