 S&P Lowers Debt Rating on Bankers Trust: The move by Standard & Poor's Corp. 
reflects concern over the bank's risky trading activities in global financial 
markets.The change, which also includes the bank's BT Overseas Finance 
subsidiary, affects $5.6 billion of outstanding debt. S&P reduced Bankers Trust 
New York Corp.'s senior debt rating by one notch, to AA- from AA. The rating is 
still one of the highest the agency assigns. But the move is considered a 
symbolic warning shot from S&P about the bank's aggressive operations in the 
