<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Foundation Health Corp.: The Sacramento-area health care provider said 
Thursday that it has acquired two Orange County workers' compensation service 
companies with more than 240 employees. 
</P>
<P>
 Foundation Health, based in the Sacramento suburb of Rancho Cordova, has 4,000 
employees and last year had revenue of $1.5 billion.It agreed to buy Reviewco 
and the Noetics Group, two affiliated companies based in Irvine. Terms were not 
disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 Reviewco, which has 100 employees, monitors bills from health care providers 
to weed out possible workers' compensation fraud, reduce service costs and 
eliminate billing errors. The Noetics Group, with 140 employees, helps 
administer workers' compensation plans. 
</P>
<P>
 Reviewco and the Noetics Group had combined revenue of about $20 million in 
1993. Kurt Davis, a spokesman for Foundation Health, said the cost-cutting 
services that the two companies provide are in such high demand that the 
acquisition made sense for his company. 
